[
  "François Pinault is honorary chairman of luxury group Kering, which owns fashion brands Saint Laurent, Alexander McQueen and Gucci.",
  "Pinault founded Kering, which started as a wood and building materials company, in 1963.",
  "In 1999, Pinault changed the direction of the business towards luxury goods when he bought a controlling stake in Gucci Group.",
  "The $16 billion (2020 sales) company, which also owns watch brand Girard-Perregaux, is run by Pinault's son, François-Henri.",
  "Pinault and his family own iconic auction house Christie's, plus a 3,000-piece art collection with works by Picasso, Mondrian and Koons.",
  "The Pinault Collection museum is set to open in the 18th-century Bourse de Commerce building in Paris in 2021."
]